</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-29_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/first-aid-training-courses-and-qualifications" target="_blank"></a>Rescue breaths involve breathing air directly into the lungs of a child or baby who is not breathing but has a pulse. This intervention is crucial as young children and infants have smaller airways and lung capacities, making them more susceptible to oxygen deprivation.<em></em>
