</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-58_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-59_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training and certification</strong> - Ensure caregivers and educational staff are trained and certified in paediatric first aid, focusing on rescue breath techniques, through accredited courses endorsed by the HSE or similar authorities.







































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular updates and practice </strong>- Encourage ongoing education and frequent practice of rescue breaths to maintain proficiency, which can significantly affect emergency outcomes.







































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-63_ pf-text-1"><strong>Community awareness </strong>- Promote public knowledge about the importance of first aid skills for children and babies, potentially saving lives in community settings.









































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-65_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-66_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-67_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
